[GASPING]

22:25.678 --> 22:28.887
Help me. Help me, please.
Help me, please.

22:29.056 --> 22:32.094
- I'm gonna help you. Listen...
- We don't have much time.

22:33.727 --> 22:35.059
What do you mean?

22:35.229 --> 22:38.472
I will be right back with you, sir.
Thank you so much.

22:40.109 --> 22:41.145
Okay, 20.

22:43.946 --> 22:45.938
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

22:48.784 --> 22:49.945
[♪♪♪]

22:53.455 --> 22:55.287
SEAN:
It's gotta be one of these.

22:55.457 --> 22:58.666
No, no, no, it's none of those.
It's a skeleton key.

22:58.836 --> 23:00.498
It's on a leather chain.

23:00.671 --> 23:03.835
- Where? Where? Where is it?
- It's on his neck.

23:04.008 --> 23:06.000
Oh, shit.

23:06.176 --> 23:09.715
- Leaving so soon?
- Yeah, I have to. Are you writing a book?

23:09.889 --> 23:11.425
- I just need my car.
- Yeah.

23:12.391 --> 23:14.553
Right away. Uh...

23:14.768 --> 23:19.012
I got this couple right ahead of you,
and then, no worries, I got you.

23:23.152 --> 23:24.734
Hold on.

23:26.196 --> 23:28.358
[GRUNTING]

23:28.532 --> 23:31.570
No, it's never gonna work!
It's bolted to the floor.

23:31.744 --> 23:35.488
Oh, fuck. I've gotta find a way
through these chains.

23:35.664 --> 23:37.997
DEREK:
<i>Sean, where are you, dude? Sean!</i>

23:39.835 --> 23:43.454
- Listen, I've gotta call you back.
<i>- Where the hell are you?</i>

23:43.631 --> 23:45.213
- What?
- The guy's outside.

23:45.382 --> 23:47.965
I got his ticket. He wants his car back!

23:48.135 --> 23:51.299
- I can't explain over the phone.
<i>- I don't give a shit.</i>

23:51.472 --> 23:54.761
Just get back here right now
before we go to jail.

23:54.934 --> 23:56.926
[♪♪♪]

23:57.353 --> 23:59.390
What...? What's the problem, huh?

24:00.314 --> 24:02.647
The thing is, I shouldn't even be here.

24:02.816 --> 24:07.652
I don't care if you're robbing the place.
I don't care. I'll never tell anyone.

24:07.821 --> 24:10.063
I swear. I swear to God.

24:10.240 --> 24:11.776
Please.

24:15.913 --> 24:16.949
I'll get you out.

24:17.122 --> 24:20.706
I need to find something
to cut through this fucking chain!

24:21.293 --> 24:24.661
Okay, downstairs, I think he had tools.

24:24.838 --> 24:29.208
- Downstairs in the garage cage.
- Hey, wait. Wait, put the chair back.

24:29.385 --> 24:33.880
- What?
- Look. It's not on, but he can check it.

24:35.891 --> 24:37.883
[♪♪♪]

24:49.571 --> 24:51.358
Holy shit.

24:52.449 --> 24:53.610
Oh...

24:53.784 --> 24:57.994
Hey, turn off the light
and put that thing back in my mouth.

24:58.956 --> 25:00.868
Just in case.

25:02.418 --> 25:03.659
Okay.

25:03.836 --> 25:05.372
Okay.

25:05.546 --> 25:07.253
You ready?

25:07.631 --> 25:09.293
Come on.

25:11.927 --> 25:13.543
[SEAN GRUNTS]

25:13.762 --> 25:17.005
- Listen to me. I'm gonna be right back.
- Okay, go.

25:17.182 --> 25:19.674
I promise. I promise.

25:25.065 --> 25:27.057
[♪♪♪]

25:35.284 --> 25:36.820
Yes.

25:48.213 --> 25:50.205
[♪♪♪]

26:19.244 --> 26:21.236
[♪♪♪]

26:57.449 --> 26:59.441
[PANTING]

27:01.286 --> 27:02.618
I'm sorry.

27:03.205 --> 27:04.616
I'm sorry.

27:10.921 --> 27:12.378
I'm sorry.

27:16.176 --> 27:18.168
[♪♪♪]

27:20.222 --> 27:22.214
[WHIMPERING]

27:27.437 --> 27:28.598
[SCREAMS]

27:39.783 --> 27:41.445
Oh, fuck.

27:41.618 --> 27:43.109
Oh, fuck.

27:43.287 --> 27:45.995
Oh, fuck!

27:51.086 --> 27:54.079
You guys get home safe,
and thank you for coming.

27:54.256 --> 27:55.963
Really appreciate it.

27:59.094 --> 28:03.714
- And you, sir, you, uh... You had the...?
- Maserati.

28:04.266 --> 28:06.303
Right. Uh...

28:06.894 --> 28:10.763
- Was it the blue one?
- The only one in your fucking lot.

28:11.398 --> 28:12.730
Of course.

28:12.900 --> 28:14.607
I'll be right up.

28:18.906 --> 28:20.442
Sir, I'll be right back.

28:20.616 --> 28:22.608
[♪♪♪]

28:31.210 --> 28:32.951
[ENGINE REVVING]

28:37.299 --> 28:39.165
Oh, fuck.

28:45.140 --> 28:46.597
What do I owe you?

28:47.684 --> 28:49.516
Hello?

28:50.479 --> 28:52.061
Here.

29:00.656 --> 29:02.318
DEREK:
Oh, that was fucking close.

29:02.783 --> 29:04.740
Where the hell were you?

29:04.910 --> 29:08.244
- He's... He's got a girl...
- He's got a girl?

29:08.413 --> 29:10.700
No, like chained up.

29:10.874 --> 29:12.615
Like a fucking animal.

29:12.793 --> 29:16.503
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- Look, look.

29:17.714 --> 29:20.297
- Oh, my God.
- But he's...

29:20.467 --> 29:23.505
He's on the way back there now.
I have to call the police.

29:32.187 --> 29:34.304
You know
they'll have your number, right?

29:34.481 --> 29:37.189
- I'll do star-67.
- That doesn't work for 911.

29:37.359 --> 29:39.271
- Your number pops up anyway.
- So what?

29:39.444 --> 29:43.404
- Dude, we'll both get busted.
- But you didn't talk to her.

29:43.573 --> 29:48.489
You didn't leave her there
for that fucking monster.

30:14.146 --> 30:15.478
[LINE RINGING]

30:15.647 --> 30:17.730
OPERATOR:
<i>911, what is your emergency?</i>

30:17.899 --> 30:20.437
There's a girl being held captive...

30:20.610 --> 30:25.446
...at 8723 Green Lake Vista,
in Portland. She's...

30:26.241 --> 30:29.700
She's chained up in his office.
She's in serious danger.

30:29.870 --> 30:31.281
Send the police now.

30:31.455 --> 30:33.913
Do you understand what I'm telling you?
MAN: Hey.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.574
<i>I understand, sir.
Have you seen this woman?</i>

30:37.336 --> 30:40.955
Uh, just please, please, help her.

30:44.092 --> 30:45.299
You did good, man.

30:46.178 --> 30:49.762
- Relax, you already did all you can do.
- No. No, I didn't.

30:49.931 --> 30:52.389
- Where are you going?
- To make sure it gets done. Oh.

30:52.559 --> 30:56.018
And get rid of this.
And our little side venture is over.

30:56.188 --> 31:00.353
I'm never so much as stealing
a piece of gum for the rest of my life.

31:04.279 --> 31:06.271
[♪♪♪]

32:01.545 --> 32:03.787
[DIALING]

32:04.005 --> 32:06.668
WOMAN [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Thank you for activating your card.</i>

32:06.842 --> 32:09.300
<i>EntYr your number
as it appears on the card.</i>

32:23.775 --> 32:27.735
You guys have a great dinner?
All right, ma'am, here's your key.

32:27.904 --> 32:30.612
All right, sir, here's your key.
A key for you.

32:30.782 --> 32:33.240
MAN: What do we owe you?
- No, it's on the house.

32:33.410 --> 32:34.901
All your cars are right here.

32:35.078 --> 32:39.163
You guys have a wonderful evening.
Thank you so much. I appreciate it.

32:39.666 --> 32:41.157
Shit.

32:42.294 --> 32:43.705
[PHONE DINGS]

32:45.839 --> 32:47.046
I'm trying, man.

32:57.893 --> 32:59.725
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

33:01.521 --> 33:03.057
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

33:10.280 --> 33:11.612
Oh, fuck.

33:17.329 --> 33:19.070
Yes!

33:27.130 --> 33:28.621
Come on, baby.

33:28.798 --> 33:30.414
Come on, get him.

33:41.269 --> 33:43.682
- Can I help you?
- Can you take a step outside?

33:44.564 --> 33:46.100
Okay.

33:47.234 --> 33:49.772
AGUILAR: We got a call about this...
- Now, you fucker.

33:50.570 --> 33:52.152
Now I've got you.

33:52.322 --> 33:54.314
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

33:54.533 --> 33:57.241
Hey, what's going on?

33:57.410 --> 33:58.651
AGUILAR:
Ma'am.

33:58.828 --> 34:02.037
Ma'am, wanna step down here
and have a talk with me?

34:02.207 --> 34:06.121
You mind stepping outside? Got a couple
of questions we're gonna ask you.

34:06.753 --> 34:08.745
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

34:10.674 --> 34:14.839
PICKETT: Is there anybody else here?
- No, it's just us.

34:15.637 --> 34:16.969
PICKETT:
How'd you get here?

34:17.138 --> 34:20.552
Go into the fucking house. Go in!

34:21.101 --> 34:23.514
PICKETT: There you go. Thank you.
- Okay.

34:23.687 --> 34:25.178
Come on, honey.

34:28.190 --> 34:29.773
CALE:
Thank you.

34:29.943 --> 34:31.184
Where the fuck...?

34:31.360 --> 34:33.774
- You guys have a good evening.
- And you.

34:41.580 --> 34:44.414
Oh, no, no, no.

34:45.000 --> 34:47.458
PICKETT: You hungry?
AGUILAR: Yeah.

34:48.335 --> 34:51.625
No, you fucking idiots!

35:02.601 --> 35:04.513
Sixty, 70, 80.

35:04.686 --> 35:08.305
Okay, Nino, your money's right there!
I'll see you, okay?

35:19.409 --> 35:20.991
SABINE:
That was a crazy night.

35:21.161 --> 35:22.948
CALE: Uh, yeah.
- Heh.

35:23.622 --> 35:26.035
SABINE:
Never a dull moment with you.

35:26.207 --> 35:30.747
CALE: Too bad you have to work early.
I have some tricks I haven't busted out yet.

35:31.671 --> 35:32.957
I bet you do.

35:37.427 --> 35:39.043
Mm...

35:39.220 --> 35:40.927
See you soon.

35:42.766 --> 35:44.382
Good night.

35:58.281 --> 36:00.273
[♪♪♪]

36:03.620 --> 36:05.282
Oh, fuck.

36:59.008 --> 37:01.341
Come on. Fuck.

37:18.987 --> 37:20.068
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

37:20.947 --> 37:22.734
Jesus.

37:24.784 --> 37:25.820
Fuck.

37:25.994 --> 37:28.611
- Yo, open up, fool.
- Chrissake.

37:28.788 --> 37:31.155
Get in. Quick!

37:31.916 --> 37:33.873
All right. So, what'd I miss?

37:35.420 --> 37:37.457
He had another girl in there.

37:37.630 --> 37:39.166
DEREK:
So who was the girl?

37:39.674 --> 37:42.291
- Some ho?
- No, no, she had a day job.

37:42.469 --> 37:44.802
She sounded more like a booty call.

37:44.971 --> 37:47.429
But he got her here so quick.

37:47.599 --> 37:51.343
Which means on top of everything else,
this guy's a player.

37:51.519 --> 37:53.556
I told you to tint these windows.

37:53.730 --> 37:57.440
Oh, yeah, I should take your advice
on more life decisions.

37:57.609 --> 38:01.819
- Hey, I didn't make you come here, man.
- No, I know. I know you didn't.

38:04.240 --> 38:09.201
- Why didn't you give the girl his phone?
- Think I haven't asked myself that?!

38:09.370 --> 38:12.704
Because I panicked, okay? I got scared!

38:12.874 --> 38:16.208
I saw that murderous shit in the garage
and I fucking...

38:16.377 --> 38:20.963
And I bailed, and it was
the worst fucking decision of my life.

38:25.303 --> 38:30.014
Hey, man, you never gotta apologize
for being scared, bro. Just...

38:30.475 --> 38:32.888
I don't know.
Make another anonymous call.

38:33.311 --> 38:34.722
No. Fuck that.

38:34.896 --> 38:39.561
For all we know, he's got a stack
of brunettes to vouch for him. No.

38:39.734 --> 38:44.195
We wait until he leaves,
and we use these.

38:44.364 --> 38:47.573
Most people forget to lock the door
from the garage to the kitchen.

38:47.742 --> 38:50.109
I forget myself sometimes.

38:50.286 --> 38:54.826
- And over here's your point of entry.
- We've never opened that window, ever.

38:54.999 --> 38:56.456
Doesn't take much.

38:56.626 --> 39:01.246
Even a quarter inch and a good thief
will catch it. Been a rash of it lately.

39:06.469 --> 39:10.383
- Do you know how to use that?
- I ain't going in there with just a hacksaw.

39:10.849 --> 39:11.885
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

39:12.058 --> 39:13.845
Just be careful, man.

39:14.686 --> 39:16.473
Look, look, look.

39:17.021 --> 39:20.890
Oh, he's leaving. He's fucking leaving.
Come on, come on.

39:21.067 --> 39:22.103
Oh, shit.

39:24.279 --> 39:26.646
Fuck, here he comes. Get down.

39:30.577 --> 39:32.284
- You think he saw us?
- No.

39:32.453 --> 39:35.787
- You ready?
- Let's go. Let's fucking do it. Come on.

39:37.208 --> 39:39.200
[♪♪♪]

39:54.851 --> 39:56.934
- Fuck.
- Pst. Sean.

39:57.103 --> 39:59.641
- The window's open. Come on.
- What?

40:07.071 --> 40:08.687
Give me a boost.

40:09.949 --> 40:11.986
All right, all right.

40:12.160 --> 40:13.196
This way.

40:13.369 --> 40:16.112
I'd like to report a break-in
at my neighbor's:

40:16.289 --> 40:19.453
8723 Green Lake Vista.

40:19.626 --> 40:21.242
Thank you.

40:24.005 --> 40:26.213
- All right.
- My fucking leg.

40:29.344 --> 40:32.212
Wait. What the hell?

40:32.388 --> 40:35.347
- What?
- There was a massive lock right there.

40:37.810 --> 40:39.642
[♪♪♪]

40:46.694 --> 40:48.777
No, no, no.

40:49.364 --> 40:51.856
- This isn't...
- Sure this is the right room?

40:52.033 --> 40:54.776
Yes, man, she was here.
She was chained here.

40:54.953 --> 40:57.661
This isn't possible. There was no carpet.

40:57.830 --> 41:00.038
- What?
- It's a carpet.

41:00.208 --> 41:01.494
What?

41:01.668 --> 41:03.330
[SIREN WAILING]

41:03.503 --> 41:04.960
Shh, shh.

41:07.674 --> 41:08.710
Oh, shit.

41:10.885 --> 41:12.877
[♪♪♪]

41:13.721 --> 41:14.757
[TIRES SCREECH]

41:14.931 --> 41:17.014
Oh, fuck.

41:22.188 --> 41:23.975
DEREK:
Go, go, go.

41:28.152 --> 41:30.815
SEAN: Come on, come on, come on.
- Dude.

41:38.621 --> 41:40.112
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

41:48.881 --> 41:50.793
Hey there.

41:51.843 --> 41:55.553
Don't let tears distract us from our work.

41:57.473 --> 41:59.180
Comportment is a virtue.

42:02.437 --> 42:04.975
You've been such a help tonight.

42:06.190 --> 42:09.228
You've earned the next stage
in your evolution.

42:12.613 --> 42:14.900
And the vulgar shall be corrected.

42:29.839 --> 42:32.206
That window, that wasn't open before.

42:32.383 --> 42:36.093
I'm 100 percent positive of that,
which means...

42:37.805 --> 42:40.047
Which means that he left it for us.

42:40.224 --> 42:41.635
Are you crazy?

42:41.809 --> 42:44.722
No, man, forget it.
Let's chill here for a bit...

42:44.896 --> 42:48.810
...and let things cool down.
Then I'll take you back to your car.

42:50.693 --> 42:53.356
Just take me to the police station.

42:53.780 --> 42:56.113
- Sean, man. Dude.
- It's a girl's life.

42:56.282 --> 42:58.148
Just make another call.

42:58.326 --> 43:00.409
- Fuck that.
- Oh, my God!

43:01.329 --> 43:04.288
- Sean!
- No! They need to see my face.

43:04.457 --> 43:06.699
They need to see this.

43:06.876 --> 43:09.289
Dude, she's probably already dead
by now.

43:09.462 --> 43:13.297
Derek, that's somebody's little girl.

43:15.510 --> 43:17.467
What if this was your sister?

43:17.637 --> 43:20.254
If it was my sister,
I'd go save her myself!

43:20.431 --> 43:22.172
We tried that, didn't we?

43:22.350 --> 43:24.888
We tried that, and it didn't work! We're...

43:25.061 --> 43:27.804
I mean, we're in way over our heads here.

43:28.731 --> 43:31.144
You know you're going to jail, right?

43:31.317 --> 43:33.775
Yeah, well, I deserve to go to jail!

43:41.994 --> 43:43.576
Look, man.

43:44.247 --> 43:46.864
You wanna get locked up,
that's on you, okay?

43:47.542 --> 43:50.205
People don't like me, don't like my family.

43:50.378 --> 43:53.212
My brothers,
they already made sure of that shit.

43:54.090 --> 43:56.833
The neighborhood dudes,
the dudes that did this shit?

43:57.593 --> 44:00.427
They're sitting in county,
waiting with nothing to do.

44:01.055 --> 44:04.139
They see my punk ass walking
through those gates...

44:04.892 --> 44:06.804
...it's open season on me, dawg.

44:12.775 --> 44:15.062
They'll fucking kill me, man.

44:21.826 --> 44:23.818
Okay, you were never there.

44:25.329 --> 44:27.195
I was alone.

44:31.127 --> 44:33.540
It's the only lie I'm telling.

44:35.882 --> 44:37.874
[♪♪♪]

45:03.409 --> 45:06.117
This place is really important to me.

45:06.746 --> 45:09.159
I don't show it to just anyone.

45:10.958 --> 45:13.871
Only when I see something really special.

45:15.630 --> 45:17.667
That wild spark.

45:33.981 --> 45:36.314
We don't need this anymore.

45:37.568 --> 45:38.775
I won't scream.

45:40.071 --> 45:41.562
No.

45:44.951 --> 45:47.534
[YELLS]

45:50.790 --> 45:52.656
No, you won't.

45:55.253 --> 45:56.494
Lift up your hair.

46:17.400 --> 46:19.813
What do you want from me?

46:21.195 --> 46:23.187
[♪♪♪]

46:24.240 --> 46:28.405
Well, your dressage, your training...

46:29.245 --> 46:31.578
...is shaped like a pyramid.

46:34.125 --> 46:35.866
You're in the middle...

46:36.377 --> 46:39.916
...learning rhythm and routine.

46:41.924 --> 46:44.632
And what's at the top?

46:47.179 --> 46:48.920
The top?

46:50.725 --> 46:51.761
Freedom.

47:10.661 --> 47:12.493
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

47:17.543 --> 47:19.250
I'm clean.

47:20.296 --> 47:22.083
I'm clean, I swear.

47:22.256 --> 47:24.248
I did it all exactly as you asked.

47:27.178 --> 47:28.544
Circular motions?

47:29.680 --> 47:31.672
Circular motions...

47:31.849 --> 47:36.389
...using the correct soap and lotion
in the order you told me.

47:50.993 --> 47:53.201
What are you doing? Go to bed.

48:19.397 --> 48:21.389
[♪♪♪]

48:48.676 --> 48:51.293
This could be anywhere.
Could be your girlfriend.

48:51.470 --> 48:53.302
She's not my girlfriend.

48:53.472 --> 48:56.556
- What were you doing at the house?
- I was robbing it.

48:56.725 --> 48:58.591
- What'd you steal?
- His credit card.

48:58.769 --> 49:00.886
Which you say you don't have.

49:01.397 --> 49:04.060
- What happened to it?
- I lost it.

49:06.360 --> 49:09.819
Evading an officer, reckless driving,
destruction of public property.

49:10.489 --> 49:13.857
A parking meter, a bus stop
and a fire hydrant. Trifecta.

49:14.034 --> 49:16.196
What's that got to do with anything?

49:16.370 --> 49:19.033
You've got a lot to lose,
like your green card.

49:19.206 --> 49:24.497
- Think I'd walk in here if I didn't have to?
- I really don't know why you're here.

49:24.670 --> 49:29.165
- To save a girl's life.
- This girl that you left tied up.

49:30.759 --> 49:32.216
Yeah.

49:32.386 --> 49:33.968
Look.

49:34.638 --> 49:36.846
You can do whatever you want to me.

49:37.016 --> 49:41.602
Send me to jail, deport me, I don't care.
She wasn't tied. She was chained...

49:41.770 --> 49:45.605
...and strapped with leather
like a fucking horse.

49:45.774 --> 49:48.357
The guy that lives there did that to her.

49:48.527 --> 49:50.109
This guy, Erendreich.

49:50.279 --> 49:54.819
Cale Erendreich, yes. The same name
I've been saying for four fucking...

49:54.992 --> 49:56.984
Excuse my language... hours.

49:57.161 --> 49:58.777
Just please...

49:58.954 --> 50:00.946
Please, go find the guy.

50:01.123 --> 50:03.661
- We're making some calls.
- Go to his house.

50:03.834 --> 50:06.042
- There's clues.
- We've been there twice.

50:06.212 --> 50:10.081
First time he was with a woman,
not the girl in the picture.

50:10.257 --> 50:11.464
He knew something was up.

50:11.634 --> 50:14.502
That's why he had
that other woman there, the taller one.

50:14.678 --> 50:17.341
- How would you know that?
- Because...

50:18.057 --> 50:20.265
Because I was watching.

50:44.833 --> 50:46.244
[DOORBELL RINGS]

51:27.793 --> 51:28.829
Can I help you?

51:30.921 --> 51:33.083
Whoa, sorry about that.

51:34.049 --> 51:35.631
Are you Cale Erendreich?

51:36.176 --> 51:37.212
I am.

51:37.386 --> 51:42.222
We're investigating some alleged crimes
in the neighborhood, possibly a break-in.

51:42.391 --> 51:45.384
Would it be okay if I came inside,
had a look?

51:48.230 --> 51:49.687
How do you take your coffee?

51:54.612 --> 51:58.026
I'm embarrassed you were called out
once last night.

51:58.198 --> 52:02.317
- I wasn't aware there was a second call.
- We rang the bell for a while.

52:02.703 --> 52:07.198
I went to the store to get milk
for the morning. I was gone a half hour.

52:08.000 --> 52:09.832
You married, Mr. Erendreich?

52:10.002 --> 52:11.334
Single.

52:11.503 --> 52:13.165
But dating, you know.

52:15.674 --> 52:19.293
But no girl chained up in the office?

52:19.720 --> 52:22.133
Sorry to disappoint you.

52:24.099 --> 52:26.182
Garage.

52:32.941 --> 52:34.933
[♪♪♪]

52:37.821 --> 52:39.028
BANYON:
Nice set.

52:39.198 --> 52:40.484
Thanks.

52:41.158 --> 52:44.151
- Something's missing, though.
- Ah, yeah, bolt cutters.

52:44.328 --> 52:47.742
- Uh, lent them to a friend.
- I never lend my tools.

52:47.915 --> 52:49.656
They don't seem to come back.

52:50.250 --> 52:52.162
He'll give them back.

53:03.097 --> 53:04.508
Sorry.

53:05.182 --> 53:08.220
- Sorry you had to see that.
- No problem.

53:12.564 --> 53:14.556
[♪♪♪]

53:33.544 --> 53:38.005
Yeah, everything's here.
Laptop, valuables, a little bit of cash.

53:38.173 --> 53:41.337
Love to tell you something's missing,
but it's not.

53:41.510 --> 53:44.253
Any reason somebody would
wanna hurt you?

53:44.430 --> 53:45.921
No.

53:46.432 --> 53:48.389
I'm just a guy.

53:48.767 --> 53:50.133
BANYON:
Okay.

53:51.854 --> 53:55.473
Now that you mention it,
I have been getting prank calls.

53:56.608 --> 53:57.894
Hang ups.

53:58.485 --> 54:01.228
Calls where the caller doesn't
say anything.

54:01.405 --> 54:02.896
Any idea who it is?

54:03.741 --> 54:04.982
Oh...

54:05.159 --> 54:08.573
Who knows.
You know, like I said, I'm a single guy.

54:08.746 --> 54:12.114
Some of the women I date
have ex-boyfriends, I figured...

54:12.291 --> 54:15.625
Say no more, it's all beginning
to make sense.

54:17.755 --> 54:20.748
Oh, you by chance eat
at Nino's last night?

54:21.842 --> 54:23.959
Nino's? That place down the street?

54:24.136 --> 54:27.174
If I want Northern Italian,
I go to La Finestra.

54:27.347 --> 54:29.805
- It's worth the drive.
- I'll check it out.

54:32.436 --> 54:35.554
Good coffee, by the way.
Better than the shit I buy.

54:35.731 --> 54:37.222
[CHUCKLES]

54:38.734 --> 54:40.066
Oh, uh...

54:40.235 --> 54:41.271
One last thing.

54:42.362 --> 54:43.694
The window.

54:43.864 --> 54:47.699
The screen was ripped open
like someone cut it with a knife.

54:47.868 --> 54:49.404
How'd that happen?

54:52.664 --> 54:53.996
Oh, that was all me.

54:54.166 --> 54:57.910
A couple weeks ago I had to break
into my own house after a run.

54:58.086 --> 54:59.998
I should hide a key somewhere.

55:00.881 --> 55:02.873
Be sure to hide it well.

55:18.273 --> 55:19.480
You're free to go.

55:20.150 --> 55:23.393
- Mr. Erendreich's not pressing charges.
- What?

55:23.570 --> 55:27.063
- Wait, so you... You spoke to him?
- I sat in his kitchen.

55:28.534 --> 55:30.742
- And you didn't arrest him?
- For what?

55:30.911 --> 55:33.904
For kidnapping, for false imprisonment.

55:34.081 --> 55:36.494
Jaywalking.
Anything to get him off the streets.

55:36.667 --> 55:38.249
Were you drinking last night?

55:40.504 --> 55:44.214
- Listen to me, I'm telling you the truth.
- Here's what I think.

55:44.383 --> 55:49.799
- This guy stole some girlfriend of yours.
- No. No. No. I don't even know her name.

55:49.972 --> 55:53.465
I can't think of any other reason
why you'd waste my time.

55:53.642 --> 55:57.181
If a newspaper gets jacked
from that neighborhood...

55:57.354 --> 55:59.641
...my first move is arresting you.

55:59.815 --> 56:04.651
Hang on, but wait. You're gonna stay
on him? Keep searching for the girl?

56:04.820 --> 56:08.484
For all I know, you got that picture off
of Tumblr. It wasn't at his house.

56:08.657 --> 56:10.774
This isn't happening.
This isn't happening.

56:10.951 --> 56:13.193
I'll tell you what's not happening.

56:13.370 --> 56:17.740
Me locking you up for making a phony
911 call, which I could absolutely do.

56:17.916 --> 56:21.455
Whatever beef you've got
with Erendreich, stay away from him.

56:21.628 --> 56:23.540
Stop harassing him.

56:24.131 --> 56:25.838
I'm not making this up.

56:27.801 --> 56:31.636
You wanna file a missing person?
Try the FBI.

56:37.603 --> 56:39.595
[♪♪♪]

57:52.803 --> 57:54.795
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

58:08.318 --> 58:09.854
Is this who came to see you?

58:13.448 --> 58:15.189
Yes?

58:18.453 --> 58:20.035
Good.

58:21.498 --> 58:22.989
You're so good.

58:29.589 --> 58:31.581
[♪♪♪]

58:57.826 --> 59:01.365
- Thanks, Sean.
- So is that it?

59:01.538 --> 59:03.245
We have what we need.

59:03.415 --> 59:07.329
So now you match her face
with some missing-persons database?

59:07.502 --> 59:11.166
- I can't discuss an investigation.
- But there is an investigation?

59:17.971 --> 59:20.930
You know, but I can identify her,
you know?

59:21.099 --> 59:23.341
If you need me, you'll give me a call?

59:23.518 --> 59:25.510
You should go home.

59:31.276 --> 59:32.312
[STAMMERS]

59:32.486 --> 59:35.069
Look, I'm sorry, just please.

59:35.238 --> 59:38.902
I just need to know that she's okay.

59:43.288 --> 59:44.870
Great.

59:49.336 --> 59:51.328
[♪♪♪]

01:00:12.317 --> 01:00:13.353
SEAN:
Fuck!

01:00:13.902 --> 01:00:16.064
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

01:00:16.238 --> 01:00:18.195
Fuck! Fuck!

01:00:18.698 --> 01:00:20.405
Fuck!

01:00:41.388 --> 01:00:43.380
[♪♪♪]

01:01:22.929 --> 01:01:24.386
[IMITATES GUNSHOT]

01:02:23.323 --> 01:02:25.155
[SHOWER TURNS OFF]

01:02:29.371 --> 01:02:31.363
[♪♪♪]

01:02:45.095 --> 01:02:47.007
MAN: <i>RYcords.</i>
- Hey, this is Fuller.

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:49.297
Can you bring
the Valkenberg file to my desk?

01:02:49.474 --> 01:02:51.431
<i>- ThY cold casY?</i>
- The trust-fund kid.

01:02:51.601 --> 01:02:54.218
<i>- Digital copy okay?</i>
- No, I want a hard copy.

01:02:54.396 --> 01:02:56.183
<i>Okay, no problem.</i>

01:03:02.946 --> 01:03:04.437
[PHONE RINGS]

01:03:04.614 --> 01:03:07.652
Nino's.
MAN: <i>What kind of place you running?!</i>

01:03:07.826 --> 01:03:09.658
<i>Scusa,</i> what do you mean?

01:03:09.828 --> 01:03:13.572
<i>My wife and I just ID'd
one of your little parking valets...</i>

01:03:13.748 --> 01:03:15.614
<i>...down at the police station.</i>

01:03:15.792 --> 01:03:19.661
<i>We eat at your restaurant, and this is
how you repay us? By robbing us?</i>

01:03:19.838 --> 01:03:21.545
What? Uh...

01:03:21.715 --> 01:03:22.751
No, sir.

01:03:22.924 --> 01:03:25.883
[IN GRAVELLY VOICE]
Cop said it's been happening for months!

01:03:26.052 --> 01:03:29.045
<i>You know, my wife works
for Immigration and Customs.</i>

01:03:29.222 --> 01:03:32.636
<i>I sure hopY everybody in your kitchYn
has their goddamn papers.</i>

01:03:32.809 --> 01:03:34.675
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

01:03:35.353 --> 01:03:37.345
[♪♪♪]

01:03:43.028 --> 01:03:45.736
What time is it? One fifty-four.

01:03:45.905 --> 01:03:47.862
She should be here.

01:03:48.241 --> 01:03:50.904
Sean. What are you doing here?

01:03:51.995 --> 01:03:54.908
- Hey. Can we just...?
- What? Oh, what's wrong?

01:03:55.081 --> 01:03:58.995
- Nothing. I haven't slept. I need to talk.
- Yeah, of course, but...

01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:02.003
- Riley, we gotta go.
- Just blow it off.

01:04:02.172 --> 01:04:05.756
I can't. I have a presentation.
It's worth a third of my grade.

01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:10.169
- Something's happened.
- I'll be done in 90 minutes.

01:04:10.347 --> 01:04:12.304
You can tell me everything then.

01:04:12.474 --> 01:04:15.217
- Okay?
- Okay. Okay.

01:04:15.393 --> 01:04:17.350
- Meet me at my place?
- Yeah, sure.

01:04:17.520 --> 01:04:19.807
- Okay, I love you, sweetie.
- Yeah.

01:04:20.899 --> 01:04:22.060
Love you too.

01:04:22.233 --> 01:04:23.769
Okay.

01:04:27.197 --> 01:04:29.564
Listen, there's no way I can work today.

01:04:29.741 --> 01:04:33.325
I haven't slept,
and I can't get iron girl out of my head.

01:04:33.495 --> 01:04:37.284
- Who?
<i>- I just can't stop thinking that maybe...</i>

01:04:38.875 --> 01:04:42.664
...we're both trapped
in that house together.

01:04:42.837 --> 01:04:45.921
- It's like I've never left.
<i>- Yeah, man, no worries.</i>

01:04:46.091 --> 01:04:47.923
It's all good. I got your back.

01:04:49.219 --> 01:04:51.256
- What the fuck?
- What?

01:04:51.888 --> 01:04:53.880
Hey, I'll call you back.

01:04:56.059 --> 01:04:58.642
Yo! What the hell you doing?
This is our account.

01:04:58.812 --> 01:05:00.303
- Not no more.
- Says who?

01:05:00.480 --> 01:05:03.018
- Nino.
- How about I kick your country face?

01:05:03.191 --> 01:05:04.898
- I'm standing here, bitch.
- Boys.

01:05:05.068 --> 01:05:09.529
- We can't have no trouble.
- Nino, what's going on? This ain't right.

01:05:09.697 --> 01:05:11.484
No trouble. You go.

01:05:12.200 --> 01:05:14.032
He's asking nice, I'm not.

01:05:14.202 --> 01:05:16.615
- Fuck you, man. This is bullshit.
- Yeah?

01:05:16.788 --> 01:05:18.404
Fucking bullshit, Nino.

01:05:19.082 --> 01:05:20.539
Don't come back, bitch.

01:05:22.377 --> 01:05:24.084
DEREK:
Fuck you!

01:05:24.254 --> 01:05:26.211
[GRUNTING]

01:05:36.182 --> 01:05:37.468
You're excused.

01:05:55.368 --> 01:05:57.360
[♪♪♪]

01:06:08.965 --> 01:06:10.297
[JAIL DOOR SHUTS]

01:06:53.551 --> 01:06:55.884
A glacier may move in two ways.

01:06:56.054 --> 01:06:59.138
The first is glacial internal flow.

01:06:59.307 --> 01:07:01.765
This is caused by gravity
and internal pressure...

01:07:01.935 --> 01:07:05.053
...pushing the glacier formation
to lower elevation.

01:07:05.230 --> 01:07:06.266
[PHONE BUZZING]

01:07:06.439 --> 01:07:09.022
Not unlike knocking over a stack of cards.

01:07:09.192 --> 01:07:13.527
As you can see, the top of the glacier
is moving faster than the bottom...

01:07:13.696 --> 01:07:16.234
...because of friction with the ground.

01:07:17.325 --> 01:07:18.782
Basal sliding is caused by...

01:07:18.952 --> 01:07:22.741
...the base of the glacier melting.
This is like an ice cube on a countertop.

01:07:22.914 --> 01:07:23.950
[PHONES CHIMING]

01:07:24.123 --> 01:07:26.115
As it melts, the base becomes slippery.

01:07:27.335 --> 01:07:29.918
Glaciers move very slowly.

01:07:31.005 --> 01:07:36.342
Most of the time,
only a few centimeters each day.

01:07:36.553 --> 01:07:38.545
[STUDENTS MURMURING]

01:07:43.059 --> 01:07:45.346
Occasionally, a glacier speeds up.

01:07:45.520 --> 01:07:48.513
- When a glacier speeds up...
- It's her.

01:07:48.690 --> 01:07:50.556
...it's called surging.

01:07:50.733 --> 01:07:51.769
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

01:07:51.985 --> 01:07:54.819
A surging glacier can advance tens
or even...

01:07:55.822 --> 01:07:58.030
...hundreds of meters a day.

01:07:59.909 --> 01:08:01.571
What's that smell?

01:08:01.744 --> 01:08:04.828
- I had to fish this out of the garbage.
- Don't bring it in.

01:08:04.998 --> 01:08:07.285
Just leave it there, all right?

01:08:08.918 --> 01:08:11.535
Sit down.
I'll get you some ice for your eye.

01:08:11.713 --> 01:08:12.749
Thanks, man.

01:08:15.049 --> 01:08:16.961
I ought to go back with my HK...

01:08:17.135 --> 01:08:20.924
- ...and show those rednecks what's what.
- Let it go, man.

01:08:21.096 --> 01:08:22.884
We're lucky we're not in jail.

01:08:23.850 --> 01:08:27.093
- Thanks.
- So how many of them were there?

01:08:27.270 --> 01:08:28.350
Man, shut up.

01:08:29.063 --> 01:08:30.474
[PHONE DINGS]

01:08:34.944 --> 01:08:38.187
RILEY [ON VOICEMAIL]:
<i>I don't know what I did to you...</i>

01:08:38.363 --> 01:08:40.151
<i>...but you are such an asshole.</i>

01:08:40.325 --> 01:08:41.361
[♪♪♪]

01:08:41.533 --> 01:08:43.149
What the...?

01:08:44.495 --> 01:08:46.361
I have to go.

01:08:46.538 --> 01:08:48.531
I'm really sorry, man.

01:09:08.978 --> 01:09:10.014
[BUZZING]

01:09:10.188 --> 01:09:12.725
Riley. Riley, can you hear me?

01:09:12.899 --> 01:09:16.142
- If someone can hear me...
- You got some fucking nerve.

01:09:16.319 --> 01:09:19.062
- I didn't do this. This wasn't me. Riley!
- Okay.

01:09:19.238 --> 01:09:21.104
She doesn't wanna talk to you!

01:09:21.282 --> 01:09:25.026
- Want me to call security?
- I don't know what happened. Please!

01:09:25.203 --> 01:09:26.944
- Riley, talk to me.
- This building...

01:09:27.121 --> 01:09:30.990
...it's for students only.
Get the fuck out of here!

01:09:31.167 --> 01:09:33.203
SEAN: I didn't do it.
- Tell that to her dad.

01:09:33.377 --> 01:09:35.085
- Asshole!
- Please, please.

01:09:35.254 --> 01:09:36.870
- Riley, please.
- Security!

01:09:37.340 --> 01:09:39.127
Riley.

01:10:07.203 --> 01:10:08.819
[TIRES SCREECHING]

01:10:19.215 --> 01:10:21.002
[PANTING]

01:10:25.179 --> 01:10:26.465
Jesus.

01:10:26.639 --> 01:10:28.631
Jesus Christ.

01:10:28.808 --> 01:10:30.549
[PHONE RINGING]

01:10:37.108 --> 01:10:38.599
Hello?

01:10:39.068 --> 01:10:42.652
CALE: <i>Do you know why you'rY not
in their little jail right now?</i>

01:10:44.157 --> 01:10:47.366
- Why?
- Because you're in mine.

01:10:47.535 --> 01:10:49.492
I will correct you.

01:10:56.711 --> 01:10:59.829
SEAN [ON VOICEMAIL]: <i>Riley,
I would never disrespect you like that.</i>

01:11:00.006 --> 01:11:03.875
<i>You'vY gotta believY me.
Just call me back, please.</i>

01:11:04.552 --> 01:11:06.259
Maybe he's telling the truth.

01:11:06.429 --> 01:11:07.840
I mean...

01:11:08.014 --> 01:11:10.722
...it's just so out of character for him.

01:11:11.642 --> 01:11:14.009
I can't believe you're considering this.

01:11:14.562 --> 01:11:17.179
I need to look him in the eye.

01:11:17.899 --> 01:11:21.358
Well, how about I wait in the car?
With a gun?

01:11:25.364 --> 01:11:26.480
[RILEY SIGHS]

01:11:26.699 --> 01:11:27.985
I won't be long.

01:11:34.415 --> 01:11:36.372
Jesus.

01:11:38.002 --> 01:11:39.459
Riley.

01:11:42.507 --> 01:11:45.500
Don! Don. I need your truck.

01:11:45.676 --> 01:11:47.838
I can explain later.

01:11:48.429 --> 01:11:51.217
- What's wrong?
- I got fired.

01:11:51.682 --> 01:11:54.766
Said I was stealing company property.
Believe that?

01:11:54.936 --> 01:11:59.180
I said, "Don Falco is no thief.
Wanna check my truck, go ahead."

01:11:59.857 --> 01:12:04.192
Found almost 10 grand
of equipment sitting in the back.

01:12:05.738 --> 01:12:06.819
I'm no thief.

01:12:07.031 --> 01:12:08.238
[♪♪♪]

01:12:08.407 --> 01:12:10.023
I know you're not.

01:12:10.201 --> 01:12:11.863
I know.

01:12:13.579 --> 01:12:16.822
Babe, why aren't you at work?

01:12:17.333 --> 01:12:19.325
I've been suspended.

01:12:20.169 --> 01:12:25.289
There's a claim that I assaulted a child,
as if I'd ever do such a thing.

01:12:26.259 --> 01:12:28.342
I have to tell you what's going on.

01:12:29.595 --> 01:12:33.430
Don, you can punch me in the face,
whatever, when I'm done...

01:12:33.599 --> 01:12:36.433
...but you have to listen
because we're not safe.

01:12:38.354 --> 01:12:40.016
None of us.

01:12:49.866 --> 01:12:51.778
[GRUNTING]

01:12:52.743 --> 01:12:54.735
[RILEY SCREAMING]

01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:01.958
Riley. Riley!

01:13:05.923 --> 01:13:07.084
Oh, my God.

01:13:07.258 --> 01:13:09.341
- Derek, call me... Sorry.
- Sorry.

01:13:09.510 --> 01:13:11.422
Call me as soon as you get this.

01:13:11.596 --> 01:13:14.805
Pack your essentials, Patty.
Anything else, we'll buy.

01:13:16.183 --> 01:13:17.890
Rowan.

01:13:18.936 --> 01:13:21.974
That thing still have
photo-editing software, yeah?

01:13:22.148 --> 01:13:25.607
- Dad says we have to get ready.
- Okay, one sec, one sec.

01:13:43.711 --> 01:13:45.452
P.O. Box 215... San?

01:13:50.968 --> 01:13:52.004
San...

01:13:58.017 --> 01:13:59.553
Sandy.

01:14:00.144 --> 01:14:01.680
Holy shit.

01:14:01.854 --> 01:14:05.768
You are not taking the car. You're not
going anywhere except the Radisson...

01:14:05.942 --> 01:14:09.856
...where I'm checking us in, then you, me
and the lawyer are going to the cops...

01:14:10.029 --> 01:14:13.568
- ...and they will believe you this time.
- We can do that after. Please, Dad.

01:14:13.741 --> 01:14:17.030
- Oh, now I'm Dad?
- I'm begging you. Please?

01:14:17.203 --> 01:14:20.913
I have to protect my family,
and that includes you...

01:14:21.082 --> 01:14:23.574
- ...not some girl we don't know.
- He'll kill her.

01:14:23.751 --> 01:14:26.619
- You don't even know her name.
- Look.

01:14:27.296 --> 01:14:30.880
You have always encouraged me
to do the right thing.

01:14:31.050 --> 01:14:35.135
This time,
I have to do the right thing. I have to.

01:14:38.641 --> 01:14:40.678
I'll meet you at the hotel.

01:14:40.851 --> 01:14:41.887
- Sean.
- All right?

01:14:42.979 --> 01:14:44.811
Sean!

01:15:02.498 --> 01:15:04.490
[♪♪♪]

01:15:11.507 --> 01:15:14.466
There will be an unholy correction.

01:15:14.635 --> 01:15:17.048
There will be fire!

01:15:36.907 --> 01:15:38.819
No breakfast.

01:15:46.459 --> 01:15:50.373
Positive match on the girl.
She went missing three weeks ago.

01:15:50.546 --> 01:15:52.253
I've run this six times.

01:15:52.423 --> 01:15:55.757
From what he told us about
the leather straps and iron chains...

01:15:55.926 --> 01:15:59.135
...it's the same MO as Phoenix,
Memphis and Denver.

01:15:59.305 --> 01:16:03.345
Your trust-fund phantom again.
